                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d185">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/8802: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-17T19:00:00+09:00"
                            >July 17, 1937—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 17—7:54 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>208. At a conference which the Prime Minister held last night with the War and
                    Navy Ministers, continued this morning with the added presence of the Foreign
                    and Finance Ministers, it was decided that direct negotiations should be opened
                    with the Chinese Central Government for which purpose Ambassador Kawagoe has
                    been directed to proceed immediately to Nanking.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
